1. Create a system self-signed issuer via cert-manager

2. issue CACert via cert-manager internal-ca

3: Create CA-backed cluster-issuer internal-ca-issuer

4. Issue TLS Certs for: 
    - dockerhub
    - harbor 
    - cluster observability stack 
        - longhorn
    - opensearch

5. Figure out a way to mount secrets and internal-ca cert to each service

6. Configure Gateway API 
    - with either internal issuer or lets-encrypt issuer

7. Setup HTTPRoute  

8. Setup BackendTLSPolicy - to verify internal tls
    - if you can't setup a backend - turn tlsverify off (not secure - man in the middle attacks)





